@database sac.guide
@node main "SAC"

        ===========================================================
         ScanAminetCDROM 1.1 (3.6.94) @{"Copyright" link "Copyright"} (c) Ralph Seichter
        ===========================================================

 ScanAminetCDROM  (a.k.a.  'SAC') was designed to make getting data from the
 Aminet  CDROM 2/94 an easier task. You enter a search @{"pattern" link "Pattern"} and SAC scans
 'AMINET_0294:Index'  for  matching entries. The result is then displayed in
 AmigaGuide  format,  and  you may view the @{".readme files" link "readme"} or even @{"unpack" link "unpack"} the
 desired archive with a single mouse click.

 SAC  requires Kickstart 37.175 (OS 2.04) or better. It can be run from both
 @{"Workbench" link "Workbench"} and @{"CLI" link "CLI"}. If you're having difficulties, contact the @{"author" link "Author"}.

 Program history:

    V1.0  Initial release.

    V1.1  Added archive type recognition and DMS unpack feature. Tool types
          are now used if SAC is invoked from CLI.

@endnode



